{"paperId": "ff34f19c8547c69c412e7391932028f9c035f30f", "title": "Improving Korean NLP Tasks with Linguistically Informed Subword Tokenization and Sub-character Decomposition", "abstract": "We introduce a morpheme-aware subword tokenization method that utilizes sub-character decomposition to address the challenges of applying Byte Pair Encoding (BPE) to Korean, a language characterized by its rich morphology and unique writing system. Our approach balances linguistic accuracy with computational efficiency in Pre-trained Language Models (PLMs). Our evaluations show that this technique achieves good performances overall, notably improving results in the syntactic task of NIKL-CoLA. This suggests that integrating morpheme type information can enhance language models' syntactic and semantic capabilities, indicating that adopting more linguistic insights can further improve performance beyond standard morphological analysis.", "venue": "arXiv.org", "year": 2023, "citationCount": 0, "influentialCitationCount": 0, "openAccessPdf": null, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "A morpheme-aware subword tokenization method that utilizes sub-character decomposition to address the challenges of applying Byte Pair Encoding to Korean, indicating that adopting more linguistic insights can further improve performance beyond standard morphological analysis."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [-0.43688368797302246, 0.49924227595329285, -0.5542586445808411, 0.2921389043331146, -0.9412233233451843, -0.4761935770511627, 0.026317527517676353, 0.1844976246356964, -0.5897202491760254, 0.12403836101293564, 0.9743833541870117, 0.026022277772426605, 0.0033308968413621187, -0.23359942436218262, 0.13779743015766144, -0.00681744609028101, -0.7108672261238098, 0.15160724520683289, -0.7487848401069641, -0.019789839163422585, -0.03704031929373741, -0.21018433570861816, -0.08933825045824051, 0.3869895040988922, 0.4308817982673645, 0.12883257865905762, -0.03234900161623955, 0.9148213